    "last_updated": "2026-01-31",
    "excerpt": "This is the Shir haKavod (\"Hymn of Glory,\" also known by its incipit \"An'im Zemirot\") attributed to Rabbi Yehudah he-Ḥasid of Regensburg, included at the conclusion of the Shir haYiḥud (first attested in print in Thiengen 1560). This translation by Israel Zangwill, was first published in Arthur Davis and Herbert Adler's <em><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/?p=27446\">Maḥzor Avodat Ohel Moed: Avodat Yom haKippurim (Evening Service)</a></em> (1904), pp. 73-74. . . .",
    "content": "<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Rhyming Translation (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">The Ark is opened.</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nא׳\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nⅠ\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nאַנְעִים זְמִירוֹת וְשִׁירִים אֶאֱרוֹג<br />\nכִּי אֵלֶֽיךָ נַפְשִׁי תַעֲרוֹג׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nSweet hymns shall be my chant and woven songs,<br />\nFor Thou art all for which my spirit longs —\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nנַפְשִׁי חָמְדָה בְּצֵל יָדֶֽךָ<br />\nלָדַֽעַת כׇּל רָז סוֹדֶֽךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nTo be within the shadow of Thy hand<br />\nAnd all Thy mystery to understand.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמִדֵּי דַבְּרִי בִּכְבוֹדֶֽךָ<br />\nהוֹמֶה לִבִּי אֶל דּוֹדֶֽיךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThe while Thy glory is upon my tongue,<br />\nMy inmost heart with love of Thee is wrung.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nעַל כֵּן אֲדַבֵּר בְּךָ נִכְבָּדוֹת<br />\nוְשִׁמְךָ אֲכַבֵּד בְּשִׁירֵי יְדִידוֹת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nSo though Thy mighty marvels I proclaim,<br />\n’Tis songs of love wherewith I greet Thy <span class=\"divine-referent\">name</span>.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nב׳\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nⅡ\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">אֲ</span>סַפְּרָה כְבוֹדְךָ וְלֹא רְאִיתִֽיךָ<br />\nאֲדַמְּךָ אֲכַנְּךָ וְלֹא יְדַעְתִּֽיךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI have not seen Thee, yet I tell Thy praise, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nNor known Thee, yet I image forth Thy ways.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">בְּ</span>יַד נְבִיאֶֽיךָ בְּסוֹד עֲבָדֶֽיךָ<br />\nדִּמִּֽיתָ הֲדַר כְבוֹד הוֹדֶֽךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nFor by Thy seers’ and servants’ mystic speech <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nThou didst Thy sov’ran splendour darkly teach.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">גְּ</span>דֻלָּתְךָ וּגְבוּרָתֶֽךָ<br />\nכִּנּוּ לְתֹֽקֶף פְּעֻלָּתֶֽךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nAnd from the grandeur of Thy work they drew <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nThe measure of Thy inner greatness, too.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">דִּ</span>מּוּ אוֹתְךָ וְלֹא כְפִי יֶשְׁךָ<br />\nוַיַּשְׁוֽוּךָ לְפִי מַעֲשֶֽׂיךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThey told of Thee, but not as Thou must be, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nSince from Thy work they tried to body Thee.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">הִ</span>מְשִׁילֽוּךָ בְּרֹב חֶזְיוֹנוֹת<br />\nהִנְּךָ אֶחָד בְּכׇל דִּמְיוֹנוֹת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nTo countless visions did their pictures run, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nBehold through all the visions Thou art one.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nג׳\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nⅢ\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">וַ</span>יֶּחֱזוּ בְךָ זִקְנָה וּבַחֲרוּת<br />\nוּשְׂעַר רֹאשְׁךָ בְּשֵׂיבָה וְשַׁחֲרוּת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nIn Thee old age and youth at once were drawn. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nThe grey of eld, the flowing locks of dawn,\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">זִ</span>קְנָה בְּיוֹם דִּין וּבַחֲרוּת בְּיוֹם קְרָב<br />\nכְּאִישׁ מִלְחָמוֹת יָדָיו לוֹ רָב׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">The ancient Judge</span>, <span class=\"divine-referent\">the youthful Warrior</span>, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">The Man of Battles</span>, terrible in war,\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">חָ</span>בַשׁ כּֽוֹבַע יְשׁוּעָה בְּרֹאשוֹ<br />\nהוֹשִֽׁיעָה לּוֹ יְמִינוֹ וּזְרֽוֹעַ קָדְשׁוֹ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThe helmet of salvation on <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> head. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nAnd by <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> hand and arm the triumph led,\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">טַ</span>לְלֵי אוֹרוֹת רֹאשוֹ נִמְלָא<br />\nקְוֻצּוֹתָיו רְסִֽיסֵי לָֽיְלָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> head all shining with the dew of light, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> locks all dripping with the drops of night.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nד׳\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nⅣ\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">יִ</span>תְפָּאֵר בִּי כִּי חָפֵץ בִּי<br />\nוְהוּא יִהְיֶה לִי לַעֲטֶֽרֶת צְבִי׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI glorify <span class=\"divine-referent\">Him</span>, for <span class=\"divine-referent\">He</span> joys in me. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nMy crown of beauty <span class=\"divine-referent\">He</span> shall ever be!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">כֶּֽ</span>תֶם טָהוֹר פָּז דְּמוּת רֹאשוֹ<br />\nוְחַק עַל מֶֽצַח כְּבוֹד שֵׁם קָדְשׁוֹ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> head is like pure gold: <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> forehead’s flame  <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nIs graven glory of <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> holy <span class=\"divine-referent\">name</span>.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">לְ</span>חֵן וּלְכָבוֹד צְבִי תִפְאָרָה<br />\nאֻמָּתוֹ לוֹ עִטְּרָה עֲטָרָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nAnd with that lovely diadem ’tis graced. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nThe coronal <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> people there have placed.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">מַ</span>חְלְפוֹת רֹאשוֹ כְּבִימֵי בְחֻרוֹת<br />\nקְוֻצּוֹתָיו תַּלְתַּלִּים שְׁחוֹרוֹת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> hair as on the head of youth is twined, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nIn wealth of raven curls it flows behind.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">נְ</span>וֵה הַצֶּֽדֶק צְבִי תִפְאַרְתּוֹ<br />\nיַעֲלֶה נָּא עַל רֹאשׁ שִׂמְחָתוֹ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> circlet is the home of righteousness; <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nAh, may <span class=\"divine-referent\">He</span> love <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> highest rapture less!\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">סְ</span>גֻלָּתוֹ תְּהִי נָא בְיָדוֹ עֲטֶֽרֶת<br />\nוּצְנִיף מְלוּכָה צְבִי תִפְאֶֽרֶת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nAnd be <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> treasured people in <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> hand <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nA diadem <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> kingly brow to band.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">עֲ</span>מוּסִים נְשָׂאָם עֲטֶֽרֶת עִנְּדָם<br />\nמֵאֲשֶׁר יָקְרוּ בְעֵינָיו כִּבְּדָם׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nBy <span class=\"divine-referent\">Him</span> they were uplifted, carried, crowned, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nThus honoured inasmuch as precious found.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">פְּ</span>אֵרוֹ עָלַי וּפְאֵרִי עָלָיו<br />\nוְקָרוֹב אֵלַי בְּקָרְאִי אֵלָיו׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> glory is on me, and mine on <span class=\"divine-referent\">Him</span>, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nAnd when I call <span class=\"divine-referent\">He</span> is not far or dim.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">צַ</span>ח וְאָדוֹם לִלְבוּשׁוֹ אָדוֹם<br />\nפּוּרָה בְּדָרְכוֹ בְּבוֹאוֹ מֵאֱדוֹם׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nRuddy in red apparel, bright <span class=\"divine-referent\">He</span> glows <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nWhen <span class=\"divine-referent\">He</span> from treading Edom’s wine-press goes.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">קֶֽ</span>שֶׁר תְּפִלִּין הֶרְאָה לֶעָנָו<br />\nתְּמוּנַת יְיָ לְנֶֽגֶד עֵינָיו׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nPhylacteried the vision Moses viewed <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nThe day he gazed on <span class=\"divine-referent\">God</span>’s similitude.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">ר</span>וֹצֶה בְעַמּוֹ עֲנָוִים יְפָאֵר<br />\nיוֹשֵׁב תְּהִלּוֹת בָּם לְהִתְפָּאֵר׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">He</span> loves <span class=\"divine-referent\">His</span> folk; the meek will glorify, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nAnd, shrined in prayer, draw their rapt reply.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nה׳\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nⅤ\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nרֹאשׁ דְּבָרְךָ אֱמֶת<br />\nקוֹרֵא מֵרֹאשׁ,<br />\nדּוֹר וָדוֹר עַם דּוֹרֶשְׁךָ דְּרוֹשׁ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nTruth is Thy primal word;<br />\nat Thy behest<br />\nThe generations pass — O aid our quest\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">שִׁ</span>ית הֲמוֹן שִׁירַי נָא עָלֶֽיךָ<br />\nוְרִנָּתִי תִּקְרַב אֵלֶֽיךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nFor Thee, and set my host of songs on high. <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nAnd let my psalmody come very nigh.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n<span class=\"acrostic\">תְּ</span>הִלָּתִי תְּהִי לְרֹאשׁךָ עֲטֶֽרֶת<br />\nוּתְפִלָּתִי תִּכּוֹן קְטֹֽורֶת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMy praises as a coronal account, <span class=\"acrostic\">&nbsp;</span><br />\nAnd let my prayer as Thine incense mount.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nתִּיקַר שִׁירַת רָשׁ בְּעֵינֶֽיךָ<br />\nכְּשִּׁיר יוּשַׁר עַל קָרְבָּנֶֽיךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nDeem precious unto Thee the poor man’s song,<br />\nAs those that to Thine altar did belong.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבִּרְכָתִי תַעֲלֶה לְרֹאשׁ מַשְׁבִּיר<br />\nמְחוֹלֵל וּמוֹלִיד צַדִּיק כַּבִּיר׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nRise, O my blessing, to <span class=\"divine-referent\">the lord of birth</span>,<br />\nThe breeding, quickening, righteous force of earth.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nוּבְבִרְכָתִי תְנַעֲנַע לִי רֹאשׁ<br />\nוְאוֹתָהּ קַח לְךָ כִּבְשָׂמִים רֹאשׁ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nDo Thou receive it with acceptant nod,<br />\nMy choicest incense offered to <span class=\"divine-referent\">my God</span>.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nיֶעֱרַב נָא שִׂיחִי עָלֶֽיךָ<br />\nכִּי נַפְשִׁי תַעֲרוֹג אֵלֶֽיךָ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nAnd let my meditation grateful be,<br />\nFor all my being is athirst for Thee.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nלְךָ יְיָ<br />\nהַגְּדֻלָּה וְהַגְּבוּרָה<br />\nוְהַתִּפְאֶרֶת וְהַנֵּצַח וְהַהוֹד<br />\nכִּי־כֹל בַּשָּׁמַיִם<br />\nוּבָאָרֶץ<br />\nלְךָ יְיָ הַמַּמְלָכָה<br />\nוְהַמִּתְנַשֵּׂא לְכֹל לְרֹאשׁ׃ <span class=\"citation\">(דברי הימים א׳ כט:יא)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThine, O <span class=\"divine-referent\">Lord</span>,<br />\nare greatness and power,<br />\nglory, victory and majesty;<br />\nfor all that is in the heaven<br />\nand in the earth is thine:<br />\nthine is sovereignty, O <span class=\"divine-referent\">Lord</span>,<br />\nand pre-eminence supreme. <span class=\"citation\">(1 Chronicles 29:11)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמִי יְמַלֵּל גְּבוּרוֹת יְיָ<br />\nיַשְׁמִיעַ כָּל־תְּהִלָּתוֹ׃ <span class=\"citation\">(תהלים קו:ב)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nWho can utter the mighty acts of <span class=\"divine-referent\">the Lord</span>?<br />\nWho can show forth all his praise? <span class=\"citation\">(Psalms 106:2)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"instruction\">The Ark is closed.</span><br />\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>This is the Shir haKavod (&#8220;Hymn of Glory,&#8221; also known by its incipit &#8220;An&#8217;im Zemirot&#8221;) attributed to Rabbi Yehudah he-Ḥasid of Regensburg, included at the conclusion of the Shir haYiḥud (first attested in print in Thiengen 1560). This translation by Israel Zangwill, was first published in Arthur Davis and Herbert Adler&#8217;s <em><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/?p=27446\">Maḥzor Avodat Ohel Moed: Avodat Yom haKippurim (Evening Service)</a></em> (1904), pp. 73-74.</p>\n<h3>Source(s)</h3>\n<style>\n       .errordiv { padding:10px; margin:10px; border: 1px solid #555555;color: #000000;background-color: #f8f8f8; width:500px; }#advanced_iframe {visibility:visible;opacity:1;vertical-align:top;}.ai-info-bottom-iframe { position: fixed; z-index: 10000; bottom:0; left: 0; margin: 0px; text-align: center; width: 100%; background-color: #ff9999; padding-left: 5px;padding-bottom: 5px; border-top: 1px solid #aaa } a.ai-bold {font-weight: bold;}#ai-layer-div-advanced_iframe p {height:100%;margin:0;padding:0}#ai-div-container-advanced_iframe\n       {\n           position: relative;\n           width: 100%; max-width: 100%;}\n       #ai-div-loader-advanced_iframe\n       {\n          position: absolute;\n          z-index:1000;\n          margin-left:-33px;\n          left: 50%;   top: 150px;\n         }}\n       #ai-div-loader-advanced_iframe img\n       {\n          border: none;\n       }</style><script type=\"text/javascript\">var ai_iframe_width_advanced_iframe = 0;var ai_iframe_height_advanced_iframe = 0;var aiIsIe8=false;var aiOnloadScrollTop=\"true\";var aiShowDebug=false;\n\t\tif (typeof aiReadyCallbacks === 'undefined') {\n\t\t\tvar aiReadyCallbacks = [];\n\t\t} else if (!(aiReadyCallbacks instanceof Array)) {\n\t\t\tvar aiReadyCallbacks = [];\n\t\t}    function aiShowIframeId(id_iframe) { jQuery(\"#\"+id_iframe).css(\"visibility\", \"visible\");    }    function aiResizeIframeHeight(height) { aiResizeIframeHeight(height,advanced_iframe); }    function aiResizeIframeHeightId(height,width,id) {aiResizeIframeHeightById(id,height);}</script><div id=\"ai-div-container-advanced_iframe\"><div id=\"ai-div-loader-